cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories as it deals with object detection in range images obtained from LiDAR sensors for use in self-driving cars. The use of neural networks for object detection suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on training neural networks using labeled data suggests that it could also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
